d Night & Black Night Apocalypse (stylized as LIVE AT BUDOKAN ～RED NIGHT & BLACK NIGHT APOCALYPSE～) is the third live video release by the Japanese band Babymetal. It contains two concerts.[1] In conjunction with the live videos' release, two live albums titled Live at Budokan: Red Night (LIVE AT BUDOKAN ～RED NIGHT～) and Live at Budokan: Black Night (LIVE AT BUDOKAN ～BLACK NIGHT～) were released on January 7, 2015, containing audio from the Budokan performances. The Blu-ray and DVD versions was later released in Europe on October 30, 2015.[2]    Contents   1 Track listing  1.1 Video release 1.2 Audio release   2 Release history 3 Charts 4 References 5 External links    Track listing[edit] The videos were released in a standard-edition set as well as a limited-edition set for "The One" fanclub members. The videos were also released on iTunes. Video release[edit] Red Night Legend "A Big Corset Festival" Tenkaichi Metal Budokai Final 2014/3/1 at Nippon Budokan (赤い夜 LEGEND“巨大コルセット祭り”~天下一メタル武道会ファイナル~ 2014/3/1 at 日本武道館?)   No. Title Length   1. "Megitsune" (メギツネ)     2. "Doki Doki ☆ Morning" (ド・キ・ド・キ☆モーニング)     3. "Gimme Chocolate!!" (ギミチョコ！！)     4. "Iine!" (いいね！)     5. "Catch Me If You Can" (Catch me if you can)     6. "Uki Uki ★ Midnight" (ウ・キ・ウ・キ★ミッドナイト)     7. "Mischiefs of Metal Gods" (Kami Band instrumental) (Mischiefs of metal gods)     8. "Rondo of Nightmare" (悪夢の輪舞曲)     9. "Onedari Daisakusen" (おねだり大作戦)     10. "Song 4" (4の歌)     11. "Akatsuki" (紅月-アカツキ-)     12. "Babymetal Death"       13. "Headbanger" (ヘドバンギャー！！)     14. "Ijime, Dame, Zettai" (イジメ、ダメ、ゼッタイ)      Total length:  73 min.   The live album Live at Budokan: Red Night was released on January 7, 2015 to coincide with the video, excludes "Mischiefs of Metal Gods", and features the new song "Road of Resistance" as a digital bonus track. Black Night Legend "Doomsday" Ceremony of Summoning 2014/3/2 at Nippon Budokan (黒い夜 LEGEND “DOOMSDAY” ~召喚の儀~ 2014/3/2 at 日本武道館?)   No. Title Length   1. "Babymetal Death"       2. "Iine!" (いいね！)     3. "Kimi to Anime ga Mitai (Answer for Animation With You)" (君とアニメが見たい~Answer for Animation With You)     4. "Onedari Daisakusen" (おねだり大作戦)     5. "Song 4" (4の歌)     6. "No Rain, No Rainbow" (NO RAIN, NO RAINBOW)     7. "Akatsuki" (紅月-アカツキ-)     8. "Catch Me If You Can" (Catch me if you can)     9. "Uki Uki ★ Midnight" (ウ・キ・ウ・キ★ミッドナイト)     10. "Gimme Chocolate!!" (ギミチョコ！！)     11. "Mischiefs of Metal Gods" (Mischiefs of metal gods) (Kami Band instrumental)     12. "Rondo of Nightmare" (悪夢の輪舞曲)     13. "Megitsune" (メギツネ)     14. "Ijime, Dame, Zettai" (イジメ、ダメ、ゼッタイ)     15. "Doki Doki ☆ Morning" (ド・キ・ド・キ☆モーニング)     16. "Headbanger" (ヘドバンギャー！！)      Total length:  96 min.   The live album Live at Budokan: Black Night was released on January 7, 2015 to coincide with the video, excludes "Kimi to Anime ga Mitai (Answer for Animation With You)" and "No Rain, No Rainbow", and is available as a limited-edition physical release. Audio release[edit] Live at Budokan: Red Night Main article: Live at Budokan: Red Night Live at Budokan: Black Night   Live at Budokan: Black Night      Live album by Babymetal   Released January 7, 2015 (2015-01-07)   Recorded March 2, 2014   Genre    J-pop heavy metal      Label    BMD Fox Toy's Factory      Producer Kobametal   Babymetal chronology      Babymetal (2014) Live at Budokan: Red Night (2015)  Live at Budokan: Black Night (2015) Metal Resistance (2016)      Live at Budokan: Black Night (LIVE AT BUDOKAN 〜BLACK NIGHT〜) is a limited edition live album by the Japanese metal idol group Babymetal. The album was released physically as part of the limited fanclub edition live video release in Japan on January 7, 2015.   Black Night Legend "Doomsday" Ceremony of Summoning 2014/3/2 at Nippon Budokan (黒い夜 LEGEND “DOOMSDAY” ~召喚の儀~ 2014/3/2 at 日本武道館?)[3]   No. Title Length   1. "Babymetal Death"   7:06   2. "Iine!" (いいね！) 4:13   3. "Onedari Daisakusen" (おねだり大作戦) 3:23   4. "Song 4" (4の歌; 4 no Uta) 5:54   5. "Akatsuki" (紅月-